Bug.WithStack:
template <class T> class A {
   typedef typename T::B _B;
};

In the above code, Selecting the T in T::B and doing open declaration returns no
name selected because IASTTranslationUnit.selectNodeForLocation(...) fails to
find the node.  Remove the typename and everything works.
This is because 'typename T::B' is the declspec methinks.
hmmm yeah, the end offset of the declspec is being set to the end of the
typename instead of the the end of the qualified name
Fix applied to HEAD for M7.

