public class Tst {
    
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        System.out.println("Click on these links to see the problem:");
        System.out.println("xxxx Tst.main(Tst.java:5) works");
        System.out.println("xxxx Tst.main(Tst.java:7) fails (\n");
       
        System.out.println("See how existing code fails to substring the link
correctly:");
        System.out.println("Existing getLinkText: '"+a("xxxx
Tst.main(Tst.java:7) works")+"'");
        System.out.println("Existing getLinkText: '"+a("xxxx
Tst.main(Tst.java:7) fails (")+"'\n");

        System.out.println("See how proposed code correctly substrings the link:");
        System.out.println("Proposed getLinkText: '"+b("xxxx
Tst.main(Tst.java:7) works")+"'");
        System.out.println("Proposed getLinkText: '"+b("xxxx
Tst.main(Tst.java:7) fails (")+"'");
    }
    
    // Existing getLinkText returns from start of link to end of line
    public static String a(final String line) {

        int paren = line.lastIndexOf("("); //$NON-NLS-1$
        String upToParen = line.substring(0, paren);
        int index = upToParen.lastIndexOf(' ');
        return line.substring(index+1);            
    }

    // Proposed fix returns *only* the link text
    public static String b(final String line) {

        int linkMiddle = line.indexOf(".java:"); 
        int linkStart = line.lastIndexOf(' ',linkMiddle);
        int linkEnd = line.indexOf(')',linkMiddle);
        return line.substring(linkStart==-1?0:linkStart+1,linkEnd+1);            
    }
}

Bug.WithStack:
This issue was previously reported as Bug#96766 on 3.1M7. A fix was applied and
released in 3.1RC1. However the fix is only partial and there is still a problem.

The cause of this issue is the logic in the getLinkText() method of
JavaStackTraceHyperlink.java. This method is intended to return a substring from
a line which contains a link. The substring should be the link text. 

The logic does not correctly detect the end of the link text and so if there is
additional text on the line, following the link, this is erroneously returned as
part of the link text. This subsequently causes line number parsing to fail.

The following code illustrates the problem and provides replacement logic for
getLinkText() which would fix the problem:

public class Tst {
    
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        System.out.println("Click on these links to see the problem:");
        System.out.println("xxxx Tst.main(Tst.java:5) works");
        System.out.println("xxxx Tst.main(Tst.java:7) fails (\n");
       
        System.out.println("See how existing code fails to substring the link
correctly:");
        System.out.println("Existing getLinkText: '"+a("xxxx
Tst.main(Tst.java:7) works")+"'");
        System.out.println("Existing getLinkText: '"+a("xxxx
Tst.main(Tst.java:7) fails (")+"'\n");

        System.out.println("See how proposed code correctly substrings the link:");
        System.out.println("Proposed getLinkText: '"+b("xxxx
Tst.main(Tst.java:7) works")+"'");
        System.out.println("Proposed getLinkText: '"+b("xxxx
Tst.main(Tst.java:7) fails (")+"'");
    }
    
    // Existing getLinkText returns from start of link to end of line
    public static String a(final String line) {

        int paren = line.lastIndexOf("("); //$NON-NLS-1$
        String upToParen = line.substring(0, paren);
        int index = upToParen.lastIndexOf(' ');
        return line.substring(index+1);            
    }

    // Proposed fix returns *only* the link text
    public static String b(final String line) {

        int linkMiddle = line.indexOf(".java:"); 
        int linkStart = line.lastIndexOf(' ',linkMiddle);
        int linkEnd = line.indexOf(')',linkMiddle);
        return line.substring(linkStart==-1?0:linkStart+1,linkEnd+1);            
    }
}
